A 30-year-old Princeton graduate has been charged with murder after he allegedly shot his father in the head and then staged his body to look like a suicide, police reports said on Monday. 

Tommy Gilbert Jr, 30, has been charged with homicide and criminal possession of a weapon, according to police. 

The son of Wainscott Capital founder Thomas Gilbert Sr, 70, was arrested at his Manhattan home on Sunday night.  

