Police sources told ABC that detectives believed the death was a homicide and that the scene at Mr Gilbert Sr's home was a 'staged suicide'.  

Gilbert Jr was arrested in the Hamptons in September for second-degree criminal contempt, for allegedly violating a restraining order. He has not entered a plea and was due in court next month, according to ABC.

